 =?UTF-8?q?=D1=80=D0=B5=D0=B9?= <stasmytarasov@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 5 May 2026 20:38:22 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat: per-instance NBT-keyed texture overrides via
 render-time sprite substitution

- Introduce OverrideRegistry mapping NBT-conditional config entries to
  atlas sprite ids (orm_overrides/<fingerprint>).
- ORMResourcePack now serves additional sprite PNGs and an
  atlases/blocks.json that adds a directory source so the BLOCK atlas
  stitches our PNGs in (vanilla merges atlas sources across packs).
- OverrideBakedModel wraps a vanilla BakedModel and rebakes each
  BakedQuad with the override sprite, recomputing UV coordinates from
  the original sprite's atlas region to the new sprite's atlas region.
- MixinItemRenderer maintains a ThreadLocal<ItemStack> for the duration
  of a renderItem call.
- MixinLayerRenderState swaps the BakedModel passed into setModel for
  the OverrideBakedModel wrapper when the current stack matches an
  NBT-conditional entry.
- TextureOverrideManager exposes resolveEntry() so the render mixin can
  reuse the existing match priority logic.

Co-Authored-By: Devin AI <158243242+devin-ai-integration[bot]@users.noreply.github.com>
